##Task 1.2

text <- og_text %>% separate(time, 
                             into = c("day", "month", "date", "TOD", "tz", "year"), 
                             sep = " ", 
                             remove = FALSE) %>%
  mutate(hour = str_remove(TOD, "(?<=\\d{2}):\\d{2}:\\d{2}")) %>%
  select(-(TOD:year)) %>%
  mutate(day = ifelse(day == "Sun", 1,
               ifelse(day == "Mon", 2,
               ifelse(day == "Tue", 3,
               ifelse(day == "Wed", 4, 
               ifelse(day == "Thu", 5,
              ifelse(day == "Fri", 6, 
              ifelse(day == "Sat", 7, NA)))))))) %>%
  mutate(across(c(date, hour), as.numeric))

  
  
print(text)

#Task 1.3

text <- text %>% mutate(sentiment = 
                          ifelse(sentiment == "Positive", 1, 
                          ifelse(sentiment == "Negative", 0, "NA")))
table(text$sentiment)
## 
##   0   1 
## 744 756

#Task 1.4

require(text)
## Loading required package: text
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'tune':
##   method                   from   
##   required_pkgs.model_spec parsnip
## [0;34mThis is text (version 0.9.13). 
## [0m[0;32mText is new and still rapidly improving. 
## Newer versions may have improved functions and updated defaults to reflect current understandings of the state-of-the-art. 
## Please send us feedback based on your experience.[0m
text_embed <- text$tweet %>% textEmbed(
                                 model = "roberta-base", 
                                 layers = 1)

text <- cbind(text, text_embed$x)

##Task 1.5

text <- text %>% select(-c("time", "tweet"))

##Task 1.6

require(recipes)
## Loading required package: recipes
## 
## Attaching package: 'recipes'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stringr':
## 
##     fixed
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     step
outcome <- "sentiment"
cyclic <- c("day", "date", "hour")
categorical <- "month"

text_blueprint <- 
  recipe(x = text,
         vars = names(text),
         roles = c("outcome", rep('predictor', 772))) %>%
  step_harmonic(day, frequency = 1, cycle_size = 7) %>%
  step_harmonic(date, frequency = 1, cycle_size = 31) %>%
  step_harmonic(hour, frequency = 1, cycle_size = 24) %>%
  step_dummy(month, one_hot = TRUE) %>%
  step_normalize(contains("Dim"))
print(text_blueprint)
## Recipe
## 
## Inputs:
## 
##       role #variables
##    outcome          1
##  predictor        772
## 
## Operations:
## 
## Harmonic numeric variables for day
## Harmonic numeric variables for date
## Harmonic numeric variables for hour
## Dummy variables from month
## Centering and scaling for contains("Dim")

##Task 1.7

text_prep <- prep(text_blueprint, text)

text_baked <- bake(text_prep, text)

##Task 1.8

text_baked <- text_baked %>% select(-(c(day, date, hour)))

##Task 1.9

write.csv(text_baked, "tweet_data_preprocessed.csv")

data <- og_data %>% mutate(month = 
                             str_extract(tst_dt, 
                                         "\\d{1,2}(?=/\\d{1,2}/\\d{4})") 
                                         %>% as.numeric(), 
                           date = 
                             str_extract(tst_dt, 
                                         "(?<=\\d{1,2}/)\\d{1,2}(?=/\\d{4})")
                                         %>% as.numeric()) %>%
  select(-tst_dt)

##Task 2.5

data <- data %>% select(enrl_grd, month, date, sex:grp_rpt_schl_prfrm, score, id) 
names(data)
##  [1] "enrl_grd"            "month"               "date"               
##  [4] "sex"                 "ethnic_cd"           "tst_bnch"           
##  [7] "migrant_ed_fg"       "ind_ed_fg"           "sp_ed_fg"           
## [10] "tag_ed_fg"           "econ_dsvntg"         "stay_in_dist"       
## [13] "stay_in_schl"        "dist_sped"           "trgt_assist_fg"     
## [16] "ayp_dist_partic"     "ayp_schl_partic"     "ayp_dist_prfrm"     
## [19] "ayp_schl_prfrm"      "rc_dist_partic"      "rc_schl_partic"     
## [22] "rc_dist_prfrm"       "rc_schl_prfrm"       "grp_rpt_dist_partic"
## [25] "grp_rpt_schl_partic" "grp_rpt_dist_prfrm"  "grp_rpt_schl_prfrm" 
## [28] "score"               "id"
outcome <- "score"
ID <- "id"
numeric <- "enrl_grd"
cyclic <- c("date", "month")
categorical <- names(select(data, sex:grp_rpt_schl_prfrm)) %>% as.character()


data_blueprint <- 
  recipe(x = data,
         vars = names(data),
         roles = c(rep('predictor', 27), "outcome", "ID")) %>%
          step_indicate_na(all_of(numeric), all_of(cyclic), all_of(categorical)) %>%
          step_zv(all_of(numeric), contains("na")) %>%
          step_impute_mean(all_of(numeric)) %>%
          step_impute_mode(all_of(categorical)) %>%
          step_harmonic(date, frequency = 1, cycle_size = 31) %>%
          step_harmonic(month, frequency = 1, cycle_size = 12) %>%
          step_ns(all_of(numeric), deg_free = 3) %>%
          step_normalize(paste0(numeric,'_ns_1'),
                 paste0(numeric,'_ns_2'),
                 paste0(numeric,'_ns_3')) %>%
          step_dummy(all_of(categorical), one_hot = TRUE)

print(data_blueprint)
## Recipe
## 
## Inputs:
## 
##       role #variables
##         ID          1
##    outcome          1
##  predictor         27
## 
## Operations:
## 
## Creating missing data variable indicators for all_of(numeric), all_of(cyclic), all_of(categor...
## Zero variance filter on all_of(numeric), contains("na")
## Mean Imputation for all_of(numeric)
## Mode Imputation for all_of(categorical)
## Harmonic numeric variables for date
## Harmonic numeric variables for month
## Natural Splines on all_of(numeric)
## Centering and scaling for paste0(numeric, "_ns_1"), paste0(numeric, "_ns_...
## Dummy variables from all_of(categorical)

##Task 2.6

data_prep <- prep(data_blueprint, training = data)

data_baked <- bake(data_prep, new_data = data)

##Task 2.7

data_baked <- select(data_baked, -(month:date))

##Task 2.8

write.csv(data_baked, "oregon_testing_preprocessed.csv")
